        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2004-02-19T17:15:38Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Transit System Flexibility Protection Act of 2004 - Permits the Secretary of Transportation to make mass transportation formula grants for an urbanized area with a population of more than 200,000 if the transit system operates fewer than 100 buses on fixed route service during peak hours.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
